<br>
             Present                             Suggested Change<br>
<br>
    Level     1      2       3        Level    1      2      3             <br>
---------------------------------------------------------   <br>
Deftness   5%,  15%,  25%               5%,  15%, 30%<br>
Subtlety   5%,  10%,  20%                5%, 15%, 30%<br>
Channel    5%,  10%,  15%                5%, 15%, 30%<br>
Fury         2%,  5%,  7%                   2%,  6%,  12%<br>
Mastery   5%,   15%, 30%                  No Change<br>
Clarity        1,     2,     3                     1,     3,     6<br>
Expertise   20,    35,   52                    20,    40,   60<br>
(no fizzle up to the lvls above)<br>
<br>
<br>
Using the suggested changes gives an increase in ability directly proportional to the number of AA points used to increase levels.  As it stands, many of the abilities give diminishing returns for the number of AA pts required to raise the skill.  I don't believe these increases would over power int. casters.  If Verant's purpose in introducing these is to keep a level 60 player interested in the game, make the abilities worth spending the time to get them.<br>
<br>
Expertise as it presently is, is practically useless since the majority of spells one would cast after getting this skill will be lvl 55-60 spells.  Spending 12 AA pts should take away all fizzles period.<br>
<br>
Increasing Clarity = decreased down time<br>
<br>
Fury - This is perhaps the most helpful in the way of allowing int. casters to do more damage in battle.<br>
<br>
Subtlety, Deftness and Channeling are not that great anyway, but would be somewhat more appealing with the suggested percent increases.<br>
